rotocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","title":"MLNOverlay"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNVectorTileSource":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnvectortilesource","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource"},{"type":"text","text":" is a map content source that supplies tiled vector data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"type":"text","text":"Mapbox Vector Tile"},{"type":"text","text":" format"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to be shown on the map. The location of and metadata about the tiles are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"defined either by an option dictionary or by an external file that conforms to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"TileJSON specification"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A vector tile source is added to an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNStyle"},{"type":"text","text":" object along with one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorStyleLayer"},{"type":"text","text":" objects. A vector style layer defines the appearance of"},{